Potato & Cheese Filling

For one batch of pierogi / varenyky dough

Ingredients

• 2 cups russet potatoes, peeled and evenly cubed
• ¾ cup dry farmer’s cheese or very well-drained dry cottage cheese
• 2 tbsp unsalted butter
• 1 small shallot or onion, very finely minced (optional but recommended)
• 1 tsp fine salt
• ½ tsp white pepper
• Pinch freshly grated nutmeg (optional, precise)

⸻

Method

Potato preparation
Boil potatoes in well-salted water until completely tender. Drain thoroughly, then return to the hot pot over residual heat for 1–2 minutes to steam-dry. No visible moisture should remain.

Rice and enrich
Rice potatoes while still hot directly into a bowl. Add butter and fold gently until fully incorporated and smooth. Do not mash.

Aromatics (optional)
Sweat shallot/onion slowly over low heat with no colour until soft and sweet. Cool completely.

Final assembly
When potatoes are warm, not hot, fold in cheese, onion (if using), salt, white pepper, and nutmeg. Mix only until cohesive. Taste and correct seasoning. Chill fully before use.

⸻

Target Texture

Smooth, cohesive, spoonable. Holds a clean mound. No moisture release.

