Dry Cottage Cheese Filling — sweet

Traditional Eastern European

Ingredients

• 1½ cups dry cottage cheese, pressed and sieved
• 1 large egg yolk
• 3 tbsp sugar
• 1 tbsp unsalted butter, melted and fully cooled
• ½ tsp vanilla
• Pinch fine salt

⸻

Method

Combine all ingredients until smooth and cohesive. Chill fully before filling.

⸻

Service Rules (non-negotiable)

• All fillings must be cold at assembly.
• Savoury fillings should be slightly over-seasoned before cooking.
• Filling must be dry and cohesive; wet fillings will fail seals.
• Overfilling is the fastest way to destroy a perfect dough.